</div>

<div class="col-xl-8 col-lg-8 col-md-12 col-12 content-section" id="content_section_9">
    <div class="service__details__wraper">
        <div class="service__details__heading text__gradient" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500">
            <h4>Investment in Portfolios</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="service__details__planning__inner service__details__text" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500">
            <p>The team in charge of portfolio finance is accountable for the administration of the company's financing connections, as well as the supervision of the company's expenditures and the structure of its portfolio financing responsibilities. Furthermore, it creates non-traditional sources of financial support.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-xl-8 col-lg-8 col-md-12 col-12 content-section" id="content_section_10">
    <div class="service__details__wraper">
        <div class="service__details__heading text__gradient" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500">
            <h4>Portfolio Implementation Team</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="service__details__planning__inner service__details__text" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500">
            <p>The implementation of TD-ICAV's worldwide portfolios is the responsibility of the Portfolio Implementation team, which include optimization, development, and administration. The team works closely with researchers to develop new systematic investing methods and improve current ones. They achieve this by leveraging a realistic understanding of markets to influence portfolio implementation decisions. In addition to this, they are responsible for managing portfolios that encompass a wide range of asset classes and investment mandates within an atmosphere that encourages collaboration and intellectual stimulation. To supervise all operations at the portfolio level and manage the introduction of new investment mandates, the team works to coordinate among senior portfolio managers, client relationship managers, and key functional units.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-xl-8 col-lg-8 col-md-12 col-12 content-section" id="content_section_11">
    <div class="service__details__wraper">
        <div class="service__details__heading text__gradient" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500">
            <h4>Conducting an Investigation</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="service__details__planning__inner service__details__text" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500">
            <p>The Global Alternative Premia (GAP) department, the Global Asset Allocation (GAA) department, and the Global Stock Selection (GSS) department are the three departments that make up our research. The GAP team is responsible for conducting research and executing the portfolio related to the alternative risk premia multi-strategies that the company employs. It is the responsibility of GAP researchers, some of whom are world-renowned academicians in the field of style premia, to enhance and develop investment processes. Researchers accomplish this by discovering new factors and refining the instruments used to evaluate current elements. The GAA team primarily focuses on portfolio management and research, both of which are associated with macro trading methods. This category includes methods for selecting countries and currencies, strategies for arbitraging fixed income, strategies for commodities, and credit strategies. In addition to managing TD-ICAV's hedge funds, the team is also responsible for managing the overlay component of the company's multiple foreign and global equities mandates. TD-ICAV's strategies pertaining to individual stocks and equity-related securities are the responsibility of the GSS team, which is responsible for maintaining the portfolio and conducting research on these strategies. Portfolios that use GSS models include long-only, relaxed-constraint, and low-volatility portfolios for institutional equity mandates and mutual funds. Market-neutral long/short portfolios of NEW-VC-NAME hedge funds are another example of portfolios that make use of GSS models</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-xl-8 col-lg-8 col-md-12 col-12 content-section" id="content_section_12">
    <div class="service__details__wraper">
        <div class="service__details__heading text__gradient" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500">
            <h4>Risk Management Team</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="service__details__planning__inner service__details__text" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500">
            <p>The Risk Management team is responsible for monitoring and managing the risks associated with firm-managed investments, including those related to the market, credit, liquidity, model, and funding. The team conducts a wide range of primary and macro-driven research. Some examples of this research include stress testing, scenario analysis, and hedging approaches. The team works closely with the company's portfolio managers to develop a comprehensive risk management strategy. This strategy encompasses macro, equity, credit, and derivatives markets.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-xl-8 col-lg-8 col-md-12 col-12 content-section" id="content_section_13">
    <div class="service__details__wraper">
        <div class="service__details__heading text__gradient" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500">
            <h4>Global Trading Strategies Team </h4>
        </div>
        <div class="service__details__planning__inner service__details__text" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500">
            <p>The Global Trading Strategies team is tasked with executing TD-ICAV's investment strategies in an effective manner. Traders, trading assistants, developers of trading infrastructure and algorithms, and academics studying market microstructure and short-term signals comprise the team. The team is responsible for developing and designing algorithmic trading techniques across a wide range of asset classes from a global perspective. The team conducts a transaction cost study of the multiple marketplaces in which TD-ICAV trades to feed the transaction cost forecasting models. Through a collaborative effort with Portfolio Management, Research, Operations, Legal, and Credit, the Trading Group aims to create and maintain a trade execution platform that is both scalable and successful for all of the portfolios that NEW-VC-NAME administers.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

